piled test runtime lacks imports for the actual classes needed. It seems like I’ll have to rely on public classes from the artifact and annotations from Lombok. The shadow loader dynamically retrieves classes, calling Util only from code injected after the agent runs. I’m curious if runtime class loading can be initiated via the service's processor, but the Utility class might not be accessible at all.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test coverage issues**\\n\\nI’m looking at the dynamic coverage report, which indicates that the Shadow loader received a 4/9 rating. It seems like the ServiceLoader is loading the annotation processor and triggering the Main Shadow class loader, but there’s no Util class available. The user mentioned that the existing test failed, so I’m considering whether we need to remove our test entirely. \\n\\nBefore making any edits, I should inspect the actual artifact. The JaCoCo report shows that the agent has transformed the classes, which indicates issues in artifact packaging that obscures visibility. I might need to delete the problematic file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "thinking", "thinking": "", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0937a963dedf3425016a4b8454b4208191995d940f166ec025\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqS4RaA0OQ2UPnwkltHskhfJW2A_okj5Ee6yIZ-vdZSNzjHxGuPxlWETIY5UZ5h79xj5Sj3cEqACLGumx0GivpaLd0J75opOhTKJm5n41CMZiDNttK1iCGshYfNHBUwbcnlwcKlIs_N0SupuOhHZXwlw6-Dub9YRqmpW7-Yjr3o-mHOTn2f-yy_DxfzcVITGptPIjycABmYTZ-xbkCZN5sOq7-27Bux-51GCx-1vWaTem2gr6g0eWWNRcbqTWv1jWRithLKrMQaJJL0FgnEtet0KXVE9oJbKvWo52691l6S-LBFxRFqP2c8gVW0dx-sZMeEF0_zEd15Qnh0VdjQxV60H45M_KDn7U136ahTQxqz4xRRXlSoL5XSFasnockGQ2jZZGr0ElDUM_ZcfUU2DZfTZYohNwL0FrYwkFKhWJgSuK6MB9itImU-JcxUJ8u17ZDi7CGlKiqS0TpCUcFcwaFh1dqdhvycXrzlrvsQr3YAmkbHxl5nDqsqUS8vpcDJ-VcJKDnNIJCDkEXHmf2os3vbXWpYIK3WIDY6zeay63esGI7Ms9_E4HojT6hMSqkwkjXAT5k7-fcf70U1enJ3QB61QNBEyaqsEcCyBBCz3WvjZD6my7C85V5YHbsXsp6VtEtEFq1afyFt7ebssstPUhN0NxHii0Fd97KMOgVmjSidLMbAeQ